cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

The paper proposes a new compact and portable deep learning network for computer vision tasks, specifically focusing on reducing the storage requirements of convolutional filters. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also introduces a novel modulated operation and an initialization method, which are related to machine learning techniques, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. Additionally, the paper discusses the performance of the proposed model compared to other state-of-the-art models, indicating that it falls under the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions the reduction of extra parameters and the use of parameter sharing, which are related to neural networks, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) another possible category. Finally, the paper evaluates the proposed model on datasets, indicating that it falls under the category of cs.MM (Multimedia).
